metadata.name: The Koi ballet
metadata.description:
Digital image of an #original painting created by the artist Lu√≠s Bastos.

"The Koi Ballet" was inspired by the #harmony and #visual surroundings drawn from observing the movements coming from #nature, an activity that is a source for the #artist to drink from, and essentially serves as a #concept for the elevation to #abstract thought. In the imagery, lakes and ponds, perhaps around Mount Fuji, are home to trout and #Koi fish, and their ballets are living spectacles, a #delight to the #mind. Work executed with synthetic enamel on an acrylic background.

Note: Physical piece already sold and not available to purchase through the artist selling channels.
